comment: Matthews (DAL) makes contact with Leonard (SAS) that affects his SQBR.
Barnes (DAL) sets the screen on Mills (SAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ginobili (SAS) cleanly steals the ball and any contact with Harris (DAL) is incidental.
Harris (DAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Green (SAS) dislodges the ball from Matthews (DAL) and any contact is incidental.
Aldridge (SAS) makes contact with Matthews' (DAL) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
RHH shows Barnes (DAL) dislodges the ball before the incidental contact with Green's (SAS) arm.
The ball is last touched by Barnes (DAL) prior to going out of bounds.
Aldridge (SAS) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and firms up his position at the time of the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Leonard (SAS) moves his pivot foot.

Aldridge (SAS) makes marginal contact with Matthews (DAL) during rebounding and he falls to the floor. Matthews then makes incidental contact with Aldridge that causes him to trip and fall to the floor.
Harris (DAL) and Ginobili (SAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Matthews (DAL) and Aldridge (SAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
LATR shows a timeout is correctly awarded to DAL prior to Curry (DAL) losing possession of the ball.
[Incidental or immaterial] Ginobili (SAS) steps over the boundary line prior to Curry (DAL) releasing the throw-in.
Ginobili (SAS) commits a take foul on Ferrell (DAL).
Matthews (DAL) makes incidental contact with Leonard (SAS) that does not affect his FOM off ball.
Leonard (SAS) makes incidental contact with Matthews (DAL) that does not affect Matthews' ability to defend.
Barnes (DAL) and Aldridge (SAS) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
